# Crypto API Server

This project provides a crypto API server that offers various endpoints to interact with the Binance exchange and fetch cryptocurrency-related data.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js (>=14.0.0)
- npm (Node Package Manager)

### Installation

1. Clone this repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/Ayushsharma199810/Assignment.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd crypto-api-server
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install
Configuration
Rename .env.example to .env and update the file with your Binance API credentials:

bash
Copy code
cp .env.example .env
Replace YOUR_BINANCE_API_KEY and YOUR_BINANCE_API_SECRET with your actual Binance API credentials.

Usage
Start the API server:

bash
Copy code
npm start
The server will start running at http://localhost:3000.

Endpoints
Wallet Routes
POST /validate/:address: Validates a given wallet address.
GET /create-wallet: Creates a new wallet.
Transaction Routes
GET /latest-transactions: Retrieves the latest transactions.
BSC Coin Routes
GET /tradable-coins: Fetches the list of tradable coins.
GET /average-prices: Calculates the average prices for tradable coin symbols against USDT.
API Response
The API provides JSON responses containing the requested data.

